author: @derwynsharp5866
text: I love the song and the video is okay.  My biggest issue is that this video is the only time we, viewers, can actually see everyone's costumes properly without the scenes flashing by 200 frames per second.  We see plenty of Lisa - I love all these girls equally with no bias - but I also want to see plenty of the others girls during the shots when all the girls are on screen.  I love the costumes but can barely appreciate them on the other three members and even backup dancers because the camera is either staying on Lisa or just bouncing everywhere in split seconds.  I just gave up constantly pausing throughout the music video just to see the other girls' with their performance and costumes and went to the making of the music video.  Again, I love Lisa but I also love the other girls; the song is by blackpink and I want to see all the members equally when they are in the same shot.

author: @Niharika._.
text:
I think the main issue is that this is their most unique comeback to date in the style and sound, yet it follows their usual formula which makes it so bland. Someone once said that BP’s producers have been trying to recreate the antidrop of whistle for their whole career and i think that sums it up pretty well - you have an amazing opening but then a slow prechorus and then a disappointing antidrop - the formula is tired.

They did them wrong. The chorus lacked climate and made no sense, the pre chorus could been more swagged out im done with Jisoo not having impactful lines and Rosè not being attuned to the BP concept. The guitar? What? Rock and Roll? What? Bruv Pink Venom had a more hiphop vibe and they ruined it. I miss the versatile Rosie, Swagged out Jisoo lines like pretty savage and don’t get me started on Jennie and Lisa. They use to fill the songs up with decent rap now it’s like we’re bagging for some decent lines and a main rapper 😂😂It was aight but not it.

Scorpion can be mostly found in desserts hence Lisa having many dessert inspired scenes.
Valorant's VIPER is similar to most of the scenes of jisoo plus she was the only with smokes and she was the only one with VR scenes Hence jisoo representing the virtual world and Valorant's viper.
Snake is found within natural caves, the black blood which always represented with the blood of snake and this is what rose portrays.
Spider is always portrayed as black creatures that can be big and sneaky hence Jennie having a huge truck and having her caged.

Instead of blowing it all on one short video, extending it would have been great, but even better would be for BP to drop a visual album with an MV for every song. The visuals of their MVs are such a huge selling point for them, so why YG doesn't capitalize on that is beyond me.

author: @themissingmile
text:
I love love love this MV, it’s probably one of their best MVs and songs. I honestly think it’s their best MV. But there’s a couple of missed opportunities which could’ve elevated the video further.

1. They should’ve started with a close up of Jisoo playing the geomungo then pan out to show the apostles. This way people can actually see it’s Jisoo playing. If not it’s hard for general BLINKs not paying attention to social media to realise that’s JISOO. 

2. They’ve should shown a clearer, more focused shots of Rosé playing the guitar. 

What was the point of adding these two elements if you’re going to edit in a manner that obscures the whole point of adding these scenes.

Anyway thanks for many many more AMAZING aspects delivered like JENLISA
